Warburg Pincus  hired Carnegie ASA as
bookrunner to explore selling as much as a 10 percent stake in
Electromagnetic Geoservices ASA.  Warburg funds will seek to sell 15 million to 20 million
shares, or 7.6 percent to 10.2 percent, of the outstanding stock
in the company, according to a statement issued today. The sale
will be done through an accelerated bookbuilding process
starting today.  The companyâ€™s shares rose 0.63 percent to 16.1 kroner as of
5:30 p.m. today in Oslo trading, valuing the company at 3.16
billion kroner ($522 million).  The Warburg Pincus funds own 21.3 percent of the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
